From: nerves_system_openwrt_one
Subject: [PATCH] mt7981 SPI NAND stack from OpenWrt main

Combined patch that brings the OpenWrt main mediatek SPI NAND patch
stack to mainline Linux 6.18.12. This is the union of:

  431-drivers-spi-mt65xx-Move-chip_config-to-driver-s-priv
  432-drivers-spi-Add-support-for-dynamic-calibration
  433-drivers-spi-mem-Add-spi-calibration-hook
  434-drivers-spi-mt65xx-Add-controller-s-calibration-para
  435-drivers-mtd-spinand-Add-calibration-support-for-spinand
  930-spi-mt65xx-enable-sel-clk

Patches were combined into one to side-step a few minor 6.12->6.18
context drift issues that broke the per-patch hunk matching
(line drift, mt6991_compat struct insertion, cpu_latency_qos call
inserted in mtk_spi_hw_init, etc).

Adapted patch 435 for 6.18 macro renames:
  SPINAND_PAGE_READ_FROM_CACHE_OP(false, 0, 1, ...) ->
  SPINAND_PAGE_READ_FROM_CACHE_1S_1S_1S_OP(0, 1, ..., 0)
  spinand_wait(spinand, &status) ->
  spinand_wait(spinand, INITIAL_DELAY, POLL_DELAY, &status)

